2026-04-29 | Minimum Swaps to Group All 1s Together

Question
Return minimum swaps or -1 if no 1 exists.
	Key Insight
Let total number of 1s = k  
Then:
we want a window of size k containing maximum 1s  
Because:
		swaps needed = k - (number of 1s already in window)
	Approach
1.	Count total 1s → k  
2.	If k == 0 → return -1  
3.	Use sliding window of size k  
4.	Count number of 1s in current window  
5.	Track maximum 1s in any window  
6.	Result:
		k - maxOnesInWindow  
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int minSwaps(vector<int>& arr) {
        int n = arr.size();
        int k = 0;
        for(int x : arr) if(x == 1) k++;
        if(k == 0) return -1;
        int curr = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < k; i++){
            if(arr[i] == 1) curr++;
        }
        int maxOnes = curr;
        for(int i = k; i < n; i++){
            if(arr[i] == 1) curr++;
            if(arr[i - k] == 1) curr--;
            maxOnes = max(maxOnes, curr);
        }
        return k - maxOnes;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Instead of thinking about swaps directly:
		think about best window  
The fewer 0s inside the window → fewer swaps needed  
So:
		min swaps = number of 0s in best window  
		         = k - max 1s in window
